article.headline: Georgia 93, Jacksonville 77
article.story: ATHENS, Ga. (AP) -- Levi Stukes scored 27 points and Georgia overcame a sluggish start to beat Jacksonville 93-77 on Tuesday. The Bulldogs played most of the game without point guard Sundiata Gaines, Southeastern Conference player of the week after he led Georgia to a 96-83 win over nationally ranked Gonzaga on Saturday. Gaines sprained an ankle with 10:06 to go in the first half and did not return. Mike Mercer took over as point guard and wound up with 21 points and 11 assists and a team-high eight rebounds. Terrance Woodbury came off the bench to score 15 for Georgia (8-1). Lehmon Colbert scored 18 points to lead Jacksonville (4-7), which has lost 23 straight road games. Tyrone Curnell scored 15. Georgia scored the first five points of the game, but over the next four minutes, the Dolphins mounted a 14-2 run to go up 14-5 on Curnell's layup. Jacksonville's Corey Claitt hit a layup midway through the first half to make it 26-14 for the Dolphins' biggest lead as Gaines went down. Curnell's power layup with 6:03 to go gave Jacksonville a 33-23 lead, but Georgia closed out the half with a 25-2 run to lead 48-35 at intermission as Mercer's drives and Stukes' 3-pointers rallied the Bulldogs. Georgia bolted to a 63-39 lead after Takais Brown made a reverse layup on an inbounds play with 16 minutes to go. But the Dolphins went on an 11-0 run over the next four minutes. They continued to whittle away, and Derek Duggins' two free throws brought Jacksonville as close as 73-64 with 9:18 to play. Georgia then went on a 10-1 run, highlighted by Mercer's stuff tip, to go up 83-65 with six minutes to play.
